race.comment: UNA GENTLE (14) went forward and gave a great sight when narrowly beaten over 1100m at Moe. Keeps improving and will take advantage of the good draw. Hard fit now and can go one better. SNAPPY BEAU (2) resumed as favourite at Hanging Rock but looked a run short beaten 2L. He's since won a Kyneton jumpout and maps well. His best form is good enough for this. PRINCE DE VEGA (6) has need the two runs back and has been switched from Sydney on a 23-day return. He has a wide gate but Meech rides and we should see more from him back to country grade. ZERCARDY (7) and CRACKED IT (13) are both debutants who have impressed at the jumpouts. The race day betting will be key with them.
